Product description

BEBIRD R1 Ear Canal Cleaner with Camera

How to Connect to Your Phone via WiFi?

If you have an Android system, please follow these steps:

Step 1: Download the Bebird app (From the APP store or Google)

Step 2: All prompts choose to allow, except "Allow Cellular Data Switching"

Step 4: Turn on the product， and click "go to connect the device's Wi-Fi" in bebird APP

Step 5: Open Wlan and connect to wifi: bebird-model-XXX

Step 6: Return to the APP, click go, and start using it.

Notes: If during your use, a pop-up prompt "Do you want to switch networks freely", select "Decline", If you selected "Allow free network switching" before using it, please uninstall the APP to reinstall it, and select "Do not allow free network switching" in the next connection process, and then proceed to the steps 1-6 above again.

If you have an iOS system, please follow these steps:

Step 1: Download the Bebird app (From the APP store or Google)

Step 2: All prompts choose to allow

Step 4: Turn on the product ，and click "go to connect the device's Wi-Fi" in bebird APP

Step 5: Open Wlan and connect to wifi: bebird-model-XXX

Step 6: Return to the APP, click go, and start using it.

Products "EAR SPOON“ of this page are covered by U.S. Patent No. D972,900 S and D974,856 S.

360° Wide Angle

360°Wide Angle and 3.5MM lens, it is a large coverage view to help you clean out your ear much easier and safer.

1080P Camera

This wax removal tool camera features a 3-megapixel high-precision camera, delivering superior clarity and outstanding color reproduction.

Light with 6 LED Chips

Equipped with a 6-LED-Chips light surrounding the tip, illuminating any area you desire to see. This tool captures more realistic images, ensuring a safer and more thorough ear canal cleaning.

IP67 Waterproof Lens

  • Water-proof len, easily clean it with swabs

Temperature Control System

The wax removal tool featured with non-heating chip,stabilize the temperature of the handle and lens at the human body temperature, it's friendly and comfortable experience to your family.

Wifi Connection

The BEBIRD R1 ear canal cleaner can work with android and iOS smart phones and tablets via Wifi. Making it easier to view your ear canal even in dam environment.

Built-in Battery

Built-in rechargeable lithium battery with type c charging port, earscope will stand by for 30 Days with once charge per month.

Packages

  • R1 Earscope
  • Canal Observation
  • Nose Speculum
  • Tongue Depressor
  • Storage Tube
  • 2*Round Tip
  • 2*Narrow Tip
  • 2*Cotton Swab Tip
  • 2*Metal Silicone Tip
  • 2*Plastic Narrow Tip

    The item just arrived and I was so excited that I opened it for use immediately. I am giving a 4 star review because the setup was a bit wonky. My phone thought the QR code was very suspicious and kept warning me to not use it, so I had to go to the play store and search for it. You first have to turn on the device (obvious, but they don't have you turn it on until the next step, so it took me a second to figure that one out as I am a bit of a ludite), and then it comes up with its own wifi network as opposed to using your normal wifi. You have to set it to "connect automatically" or you'll have problems. In conclusion, while the setup was quick and simple overall, it took some figuring out and people who struggle with technology (intuitively) will probably have some issues.

    I took off 1 star for the poor set up, but no more, as I didn't buy this item to see how compatible it was with my phone (pixel 6 pro). I bought this item to clean my ears, which it did very well! I'm sad to say that my ears are apparently much cleaner than those people with the super satisfying videos pulling out massive chunks and blockages, but I suppose that's not a bad thing. Just oddly disappointing.. got one good chunk from one ear, but nothing to write home about.

    Worked great for one use
    Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2024
    1. 0:06
    Short summary: The camera and additional pieces were fantastic and great for capturing HD photos and keeping an eye on things in the ears/nose/throat ENT stuff you may have going on. Unfortunately, mine stopped working very soon after getting it, though I did get at least... See more
    Short summary: The camera and additional pieces were fantastic and great for capturing HD photos and keeping an eye on things in the ears/nose/throat ENT stuff you may have going on. Unfortunately, mine stopped working very soon after getting it, though I did get at least one good use. I'm trying to get it to work or exchanged, currently.

    Thorough review / more details:

    Camera - The camera quality was amazing! Way better than my last one! I'll put comparison photos in the attached, but i'll also compare the two by name below if you want to skip the images.

    Tool attachments - It comes with a soft safety cover for looking up your nose and your ears, and even has a tongue depressor for looking in your mouth. The attachments for tool usage screw on which feels safer to me than my previous one that I slipped a little silicone cover on (which the metal broke through at one point after much use - I don't think that will be an issue with these attachments.) I was able to safely get a good view of my eardrum, comfortably up my nose to get a clear view of the middle turbinate. There are manual accessories but they are hard/metal/etc so please be careful if you use them.

    Use case - My symptoms I checked on were my itchy ear canals, trouble breathing through my nose, and wisdom teeth coming in late. For my nose, I have allergies (treated/managed) and always feel \stuffy and wondered if my previous diagnosis of deviated septum applied, or something else going on, to have my own view and clear photos to compare to different doctor opinions on my nose situation. I found a doctor site with different condition photos that are the same style as what we see with the app here so I was able to compare myself. For my ears, with this higher quality camera I was able to see more detail and how incredibly red my ear canals are, but otherwise don't see any issues I can identify. I have hearing loss but I don't know enough to judge based on the view of my eardrum, just that I was able to get a good look with this product and get photos. For the mouth tool, I got a high quality close up look at my wisdom tooth breaking through my gums. It'll be helpful in monitoring to see when I have to get surgery and have them removed, because currently I am prioritizing other things. I love having this to keep an eye on stuff myself.

    Beta tools - I didn't have a chance to try them before it stopped working, but they are interesting to me.

    Comfort/safety - The attachments for the top seem like a better design than the previous one I had. I don't think they will fall off easily and feel safe in that regard. However, they are not as soft as the silicone tips from the last one I had.

    Battery/connectivity - It started having issues after the first use. Even though it said it had over 60% battery, and I checked the troubleshooting notes in the user guide, none of that mattered and it turned off unless i was actively holding the button.

    Customer service - I tried reaching out to customer service through the app and just received an automated initial response that reappeared as the most previous message whenever it refreshed. Something strange along those lines / unhelpful. It also gave the option to attach videos but wouldn't actually send them, from what I could tell (even short 6 second ones.)

    Return/Exchange/Refund - I am going to try charging it fully and if it still doesn't work, I will attempt an exchange first because of the superior camera quality and attachments. If I still have issues, I will try to find a comparable product or try customer service again.

    Comparing two products - the previous one I had (which I guess isn't on Amazon anymore but still) was from the company LEIPUT, and the app for it was 'Suear' (with an ear as the app icon.) This BEBIRD product app is 'bebird' (has a hummingbird icon.) My previous tool I had for 6 months before it stopped working. This one I had one or two days... but I do like the product more so I'm hoping I can figure it out / have a working one. I have a 6 second video of the current issue i'm having with this product in the attached to this review if anyone wants to see it.

    My recommendation for use - Definitely do not go closer to the eardrum than in my photo, and I only went that close with the safety attachment (black and soft silicone, not the firmer screw-on tool for getting earwax, the one just for looking.) For the nose, it's probably not good to go past the middle turbinate. Getting a good look at mine with the safety attachment is about as far as I felt comfortable going for a view in my nose. For a better look at any of these, or if you have any concerns, see an ENT doctor (Ear Nose Throat doctor). Note that if you are concerned about money and live in the US, there is likely a financial assistance program in place that will provide a discount proportionate to your FPL (Federal Poverty Level / income.) I do like this product but it's for extra insight, not replacing proper medical care :)

    I hope this helped! I'll try to update this later :)

    Update: I charged it and it still didn't work :/ I'll reach out to Amazon.
